This species was recorded at three sites in central and northern Mozambique . The male had bright orange axillary tufts in the armpits. Peak echolocation frequencies were 102.2 kHz (female; ANABAT, n = 1) and 104 kHz (male; Pettersson D240x, n = 1) 3–5 kHz lower than in South Africa ( Schoeman and Jacobs, 2008 ;
Monadjem et al. , 2010
